CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17, reads: "Talking To Worker - Lucius Davenport, who won the Republican nomination in Tuesday's primary elections is shown talking to a worker at the polls.  He won the nomination for constable of the Fifth Ward in a heated contest."
TitMainTitle: Lucius "Lu" Davenport talking to elderly woman outside of polling place during 1955 primary elections
